      <td height=12></td>
      <td colspan=8></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td height=649></td>
      <td></td>
      <td width=426 height=810 colspan=4 rowspan=10 valign=top align=left>
        
        <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr>
            <td width=4 height=4></td>
            <td width=418></td>
            <td width=4></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td height=802></td>
            <td width=418 height=802 valign=top align=left>

<p align=left><font face="Times New Roman" size=2>The Master of Business Administration degree at Idaho State University (ISU) is designed to prepare students for leadership roles in all areas of business requiring skilled, ethical decision-making and analytical abilities. The program emphasizes the development of critical thinking skills in a supportive professional environment. Individuals interested in expanding their career potential and improving their business acumen will find much to recommend ISU&#39;s MBA program. <br>
<br>
The ISU College of Business provides the advantages of a small, quality program accredited by the American Assembly of Collegiate Schools of Business (AACSB). The typical MBA class is a diverse group of 30 or fewer students representing all regions of the U.S. and many foreign countries. The informal, friendly atmosphere encourages interaction between students and faculty, providing an ideal educational environment. <br>
<br>
Idaho State University is located in Pocatello, a community of 50,000. Pocatello is the transportation, industrial, and trade center of southeastern Idaho. It is also convenient to the Idaho National Engineering Laboratory, a nationally recognized energy management research center. The surrounding area provides ideal opportunities for all forms of outdoor recreation including access to some of the finest skiing in the country and to Grand Teton and Yellowstone National Parks. <br>
<br>
The MBA Program<br>
<br>
The program is designed to develop leadership and interpersonal skills. It also enhances abilities to carry out effective financial analyses, thoroughly understand the process of creating and delivering quality goods and services, and attain a global view of decision-making. <br>
<br>
The MBA program consists of seven first-year graduate core courses (MBA I) and ten second-year courses (MBA II). Students may select either a General Management or an Accounting option for their program. <br>
<br>
The first-year core courses develop a broad competence in the functional fields of business. This core provides a foundation for the integrative focus of the program&#39;s second year. The majority of first year courses are waived for recent graduates of AACSB accredited institutions. <br>
<br>
The second year consists of six required and four elective courses. The courses are designed to provide the student with the ability to make sound business decisions with an appreciation for the complexity of modern global competition. Traditional issues of business are considered along with concrete examples of global competition and ethical behavior. Team problem-solving and leadership skills are particularly emphasized in the second year program.</p></font>
            </td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td height=4></td>
