          <tr>
            <td width=4 height=4></td>
            <td width=418></td>
            <td width=4></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td height=802></td>
            <td width=418 height=802 valign=top align=left>

<p align=left><font face="Times New Roman" size=2>Students choosing the Accounting option will join one of the country&#39;s most outstanding programs. ISU&#39;s accounting students have an excellent track record. They have consistently placed among the top ten schools in the nation in their pass rate on the CPA examination. <br>
<br>
The opportunity for students to combine an accounting emphasis with their MBA comes in direct response to the needs expressed by the CPA profession for a broader education beyond the in-depth expertise in accounting. ISU is in the vanguard of institutions providing programs to meet the new 150 credit hour requirement for the CPA certificate. <br>
<br>
The accounting emphasis combines the MBA II core with four graduate accounting courses. This combination of courses prepares students for both the CPA and CMA examinations. <br>
<br>
Students with a recent undergraduate degree in accounting can complete the program in twelve months, including the CPA examination in May and the CMA examination in June or December. Students with other degrees have a longer program including five undergraduate accounting courses taken along with the MBA I courses.</p></font>

