    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td height=47></td>
      <td width=555 height=47 colspan=2 rowspan=1 valign=top align=left>
        <map name="map1405">
          <area shape="rect" coords="15,25,39,38" href="page8.html">
          <area shape="rect" coords="9,17,39,47" href="page8.html">
        </map>
        <img width=554 height=48 border=0 src="img69.gif" usemap="#map1405">
      </td>
      <td></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td height=870></td>
      <td width=543 height=870 colspan=1 rowspan=1 valign=top align=left>
        
        <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr>
            <td width=4 height=4></td>
            <td width=535></td>
            <td width=4></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td height=862></td>
            <td width=535 height=862 valign=top align=left>

<p align=left><font face="Times New Roman" size=2>The rapidly changing technology available to businesses challenges business education to remain current so that graduates are ready to move into the new business environment. Most business schools lack the resources to meet this challenge. Nationally, budgets for education are not sufficient to keep pace with the business world. The ISU College of Business is fortunate to have generous business partners and alumni who have permitted us to respond to the challenge. <br>
<br>
Thanks to the generosity of The J.A. and Kathryn Albertson Foundation and Microsoft, Inc., the College of Business is poised to leap into the twenty-first century. These grants have driven the upgrading of technological capabilities of our faculty and classrooms. The Albertson Foundation contributed $100,000 to upgrade classroom hardware. Microsoft donated over $1,000,000 in the latest software allowing the faculty to use that hardware effectively.<br>
<br>
When these projects are completed, the College will have 13 classrooms equipped with state-of-the-art computers and digital projectors. Instructors and students will have direct access to the Internet and multimedia education tools to enhance their in-class learning experiences.<br>
<br>
One classroom has been designed for electronic teamwork. Eight cubicles with multimedia computers allow faculty to design classes in which students are assigned to different &quot;offices&quot; to work as teams researching problems, accessing data bases, or simulating business activities. An additional computer and digital projection system at the front of the room allows the instructor and student teams to present to the entire class.</font><font face="Times New Roman" size=1><br>
<br>
</font><font face="Times New Roman" size=2>College of Business faculty are excited with the potential for new approaches to teaching made possible by these resources. We can now schedule all business classes in rooms with cutting edge technology. The success in using this technology will depend on the faculty&#39;s developing new competencies, new teaching approaches, and new software tools.</font><font face="Times New Roman" size=1><br>
<br>
</font><font face="Times New Roman" size=2>The College has always striven to provide an excellent education for its graduates. We have been able to attract superior faculty who work together extremely well to remain on the cutting edge of technology and to keep the curriculum current and relevant to the business environment. We have been fortunate.&nbsp; In addition to staying abreast of technological developments and hiring of strong faculty, we maintain undergraduate and MBA programs at a favorable faculty/student ratio to ensure personal interaction with students.&nbsp; This provides exceptional learning experiences both in the classroom and through direct student-teacher contacts.<br>
<br>
We are proud of the education that we have been able to provide over several decades and believe most alumni have found their ISU education has provided a competitive advantage leading to success. Our faculty has also been very active in providing service to businesses and professional organizations. <br>
</font><font face="Times New Roman" size=1><br>
</font><font face="Times New Roman" size=2>Striving for excellence is a continuous activity requiring synergistic interaction among many partners, including the faculty, students, businesses and alumni. Much more can be accomplished when multiple skills and resources are combined. No piece of the partnership can accomplish excellence alone.<br>
<br>
We need to ensure the interaction we have enjoyed intensifies to meet the new demands.&nbsp; For example, the new technology available in classrooms will be underutilized unless we expend time and resources to develop effective specialized software that simulates actual business problems and processes. Faculty must continuously develop competencies in the new technologies. Businesses can help by providing relevant problems and information to be used in the classrooms. Everyone can help by providing the financial resources necessary to take advantage of the technology.</p></font>
            </td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td height=4></td>
            <td colspan=2></td>
          </tr>
        </table>



      </td>
