<p align=left><font face="Times New Roman" size=1>+The Simplot Decision Support Center (SDSC) is an example of how your College of Business uses donated funds.&nbsp; In November 1995, we described what the center had been doing in its research role. We have provided over 100 sessions for local, national, and international organizations and conducted research for the Idaho National Engineering Laboratory. We have even been recognized as a National Information Systems Security Resource Center<br>
<br>
The SDSC also is integral to the general operation of the College of Business. The college is a responsible steward of resources. We have taken the original gift from the Simplot Corporation and multiplied it 25 fold. This has allowed the SDSC to be not only independent of state funding but to support students, faculty, the college, university, and state in the following ways. <br>
