            <td height=862></td>
            <td width=549 height=862 valign=top align=left>

<p align=center><center><B><font face="Times New Roman" size=3>ISU Students Succeed on the CPA Examination</B><br>
</center></p><p align=left><br>
Once again ISU accounting students have excelled on the CPA examination. Out of 17 students taking the May, 1996 examination, 7 passed the entire examination (41&#37;) and 10 either passed or conditioned it (65&#37;). Nationally, the pass rate is about 16&#37; and the pass or condition rate 25&#37;.<br>
<br>
These statistics are more impressive when put into the context of expectations based on college entrance scores. The National Association of State Boards of Accountancy (NASBA) divides CPA examination candidates into three categories based on the ACT college admission scores.&nbsp; ISU students are in the lowest category.&nbsp; According to NASBA, that category has a success rate that is 50&#37; of the national average.&nbsp; Thus, if the national average pass rate for May is the typical 20&#37;, students with similar ACT scores as ISU would have a pass rate of only 10&#37;.<br>
<br>
According to Dr. Ken Smith, the reasons for ISU students&#39; success continue to be their dedicated work ethic and rigorous, innovative course work that encourages them to analyze situations rather than memorize rules and facts.</p></font>
            </td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td height=4></td>
            <td colspan=2></td>
          </tr>
        </table>



      </td>
