            <td width=418 height=802 valign=top align=left>


















            
























<p align=left><font face="Times New Roman" size=2>In the General Management Option the four elective courses can be used to develop specific interests or to meet particular individual needs. Electives may be selected from any of the traditional areas of business (Accounting, Marketing, Management, Operations, Finance), or may come from cross-disciplinary courses such as Computer Information Systems, Project Management, Technology Management, or Entrepreneurship. A variety of choices is also available from colleges outside business such as Health Care Administration, Hazardous Waste Management, and Public Administration.</p></font>

