<HTML>

<HEAD>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word ">

<META NAME="BUILD" CONTENT="Feb 10 1995">

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Nathan Wingert">

<META NAME="DOCCOMM" CONTENT="">

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="CREATIM" CONTENT="1995:7:25:8:34:">

<META NAME="VERSION" CONTENT="1">

<TITLE><B>MBA I</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<H3><B>MBA I</B> (21 hours)</H3>
<HR>

<P>
MBA I courses are the first year courses that form the foundation
for advanced study. These courses are offered on a rotating basis
between Pocatello and Idaho Falls.
<UL>
<LI>MBA 610 Applied Economics
<LI>MBA 611 Financial Reporting and Managerial Accounting
<LI>MBA 612 Human Behavior in Organizations
<LI>MBA 613 Marketing
<LI>MBA 614 Information Systems
<LI>MBA 615 Finance
<LI>MBA 616 Mfg Competitiveness &amp; Industrial Analysis
</UL>

<H3>Waiver of MBA I Requirements:</H3>

<P>
Students who have a recent degree will have courses waived where
equivalency of content with the ISU MBA core can be established.
Students with older business degrees may waive courses by examination
or by taking a three credit hour refresher course. Full-time students
in this category should begin their program in summer term. Work
experience is not a basis for waiving MBA I coursework. Students
with substantial work experience may demonstrate competence in
a particular field through examination.<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<A HREF="page24.html" >Back to the MBA Overview Page </A><P><A HREF="page25.html" >Back to the MBA General Option Page </A><P>
<A HREF="page26.html" >Back to the MBA Accounting Option Page </A><P>
</ADDRESS>

</BODY>

</HTML>

