<HTML>

<HEAD>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word ">

<META NAME="BUILD" CONTENT="Feb 10 1995">

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="The Center For Decision Support">

<META NAME="DOCCOMM" CONTENT="">

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word ">
<META NAME="BUILD" CONTENT="Feb 10 1995">
<META NAME="CREATIM" CONTENT="1995:7:25:8:58:">

<META NAME="VERSION" CONTENT="1">
<TITLE>MBA Course Descriptions</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<H2>Course Descriptions</H2>
<HR>

<H3>MBA I Courses:</H3>

<P>
<B>MBA 610 Applied Economics</B>. Applied principles and techniques
of analysis in micro and macro economics.
<P>
<B>MBA 611 Financial Reporting and Managerial Accounting</B>.
Accounting concepts integrated with understanding of financial
reports. Use of Accounting information in managerial decision
making and control.
<P>
<B>MBA 612 Human behavior in Organizations</B>. Study of human
behavior in organizations. Decision making and problem solving,
interpersonal relations and communications, and negotiations.
<P>
<B>MBA 613 Marketing</B>. Analysis of forces producing changes
in general business conditions. Principles of market driven decision
making. Application to marketing management decisions and marketing
strategy.
<P>
<B>MBA 614 Information Systems</B>. Study of information systems
in organizations. Development and management of decision support
systems, information technology, and business models.
<P>
<B>MBA 615 Finance</B>. Study of the allocation of scarce resources,
domestic and international financial management.
<P>
<B>MBA 616 Manufacturing Competitiveness &amp; Industrial Analysis
</B>. Study of factors critical to understanding industry characteristics
and dynamics. The determinants of manufacturing competitiveness
in a global environment.
<H3>MBA II Courses:</H3>

<P>
<I>A student must complete all MBA I requirements before enrolling
in any MBA II courses.</I>
<P>
<B>MBA 621 The Decision Making Environment</B>. Study of the environment
in which managerial decision are made. Issues of leadership, values,
regulation, corporate culture and process, and organizational
diversity.
<P>
<B>MBA 622 Managerial Decision Analysis I</B>. Integrated analysis
of a firm's decisions with emphasis on the financial aspects of
these decisions.
<P>
<B>MBA 623 Managerial Decision Analysis II</B>. Integrated analysis
of a firm's decisions with emphasis on the marketing and distribution
aspects of these decisions over time. Analysis of decisions involving
product development and market strategy.
<P>
<B>MBA 624 Management of Quality and Technology</B>. A systems
perspective of the principles of quality management with emphasis
on the philosophy of continuous improvement. Decisions regarding
identification, adoption, and implementation of process technology.
<P>
<B>MBA 625 Managerial Information and Control Systems</B>. The
managerial and strategic use of information systems. The impact
of information systems on organizational behavior and decision
making.
<P>
<B>MBA 626 Business Policy/Strategy in a Global Environment</B>.
Strategic management of the firm, with emphasis on cultural diversity,
industry analysis, and strategy formulation in a global environment.
<H3>600 Level MBA Electives</H3>

<P>
<B>ACCT 631 Accounting Theory</B>. Study of accounting conceptual
framework and accounting principles. Case discussions and research
into contemporary accounting literature.
<P>
<B>ACCT 632 Advanced Auditing</B>. Integration of auditing concepts
in case discussions. Research into contemporary auditing literature
and data bases.
<P>
<B>ACCT 633 Legal Environment of Accounting</B>. Legal issues
facing accountants, including business law, forms of organizations,
and regulatory requirements.
<P>
<B>ACCT 634 Seminar in Accounting</B>. Capstone course integrating
special problems of financial, managerial, and tax accounting.
Emphasis on analytical and communication skills.
<P>
<B>MBA 691 Seminar in Business </B>
<H6>Topics:</H6>

<UL>
<LI>Project Management
<LI>Entrepreneurship
<LI>New Product Development
<LI>Human Relations Management
<LI>Quantitative Methods
<LI>Non-Profit Marketing
<LI>Technology Management
<LI>Regulatory Issues in Business
</UL>

<P>
<B>MBA 692 Independent Study </B>
<P>
<B>MBA 639 MBA Paper </B>
<P>
<B>MBA 650 Thesis</B><HR>

