<META NAME="VERSION" CONTENT="1">
<TITLE>Admission</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<H3>Admission</H3>
<HR>

<P>
Admission to the MBA program is open to anyone holding a baccalaureate
degree from an accredited institution. Applicants are required
to submit official copies of all undergraduate transcripts, a
resume, and a Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT) score.
Foreign students are also required to submit a Test of English
as a Foreign Language Score (TOEFL).
<P>
Admission to the MBA program is granted only to students showing
high promise of success. The College of Business uses various
measures of high promise, including the candidate's performance
on the GMAT, upper-division grade-point average, and work experience.
Ordinarily such measures, along with other reasonable indications
of promise, will be used in combination to arrive at a final judgment.
<HR>

