<TITLE>Expenses</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word ">

<META NAME="BUILD" CONTENT="Feb 10 1995">

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="The Center For Decision Support">

<META NAME="DOCCOMM" CONTENT="">

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word ">
<META NAME="BUILD" CONTENT="Feb 10 1995">
<META NAME="CREATIM" CONTENT="1995:7:25:9:">

<META NAME="VERSION" CONTENT="1">

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<H3>Expenses</H3>
<HR>

<P>
Although tuition costs are subject to change, the fees for the
1994-95 school year can be used as a guide: $1,134 per semester
for resident graduate students or $3,384 per semester for nonresidents.
Part-time students taking seven credits or fewer pay $97 per credit
for resident graduate students or $172 for nonresidents. Room
and board for single students is about $1,700 per semester. On-campus
apartments for married students start at $220 per month. Off-campus
housing close to the university is available. <HR>

