<HEAD>
<TITLE>Financial Assistance and Placement</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word ">

<META NAME="BUILD" CONTENT="Feb 10 1995">

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="The Center For Decision Support">

<META NAME="CREATIM" CONTENT="1995:7:25:8:44:">

<META NAME="VERSION" CONTENT="1">

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<H3>Financial Assistance and Placement</H3>
<HR>

<P>
Several one year graduate assistantships are available to full
time students.  These normally involve twenty hours of work per
week in a teaching or research capacity.  The stipend is approximately
$6,100 for a nine month academic year, plus waiver of all tuition
fees.  Applications are available from the MBA office and are
due by April 15. Awards are normally made by May 15.  Information
on other financial aid may be obtained from the ISU Financial
Aid Office, P.O. Box 8077, Idaho State University, Pocatello,
ID 83209.
<H3>Placement</H3>

<P>
ISU maintains a placement service that assists students in placement
activities.<HR>

