Microsoft is honored to sponsor the 1997 ACM contest.  
Starting with its first regional contest in 1970, the ACM Programming Contest has become the oldest and 
largest programming competition for the world's
universities and colleges. The contest is an annual event with two levels of competition. Regional Contests 
run from late October through early December.
Regional winners advance to the Contest Finals to compete for scholarships and recognition.
