<P>

<font size=3>
<b>Welcome to the Fall 1997 Instructional Grant Program </b></font>
<br> 
<font size=2>
Microsoft sponsors the Instructional Grant Program to reward colleges and universities for their innovation and effectiveness at integrating new technologies into their courses.  Grants provide languages, tools, application and system software licenses to support computer science, engineering, information systems, math, science and business courses.  In exchange for the software licenses, faculty agree to provide curriculum resources and materials for sharing with other faculty at our Academic Cooperative Web site. 
<P>  
</font>
<font size=3><b>Table of Contents</b></font><BR><font size=2>
<IMG SRC="gifs/bullet.gif" ALIGN=bottom WIDTH="5" HEIGHT="8" BORDER="0"> <a href="#01">Grant Description and Requirements</a><BR>
<IMG SRC="gifs/bullet.gif" ALIGN=bottom WIDTH="5" HEIGHT="8" BORDER="0"> <a href="#02">Faculty Qualifications</a> <BR>
<IMG SRC="gifs/bullet.gif" ALIGN=bottom WIDTH="5" HEIGHT="8" BORDER="0"> <a href="#03">Faculty Requirements</a><BR>
<IMG SRC="gifs/bullet.gif" ALIGN=bottom WIDTH="5" HEIGHT="8" BORDER="0"> <a href="#04">Upgrading Software</a><BR>
<IMG SRC="gifs/bullet.gif" ALIGN=bottom WIDTH="5" HEIGHT="8" BORDER="0"> <a href="#05">Time Line</a><BR>
<IMG SRC="gifs/bullet.gif" ALIGN=bottom WIDTH="5" HEIGHT="8" BORDER="0"> <a href="#06">How to Apply</a><p>

Please read all Grant Program documents before downloading the online grant application. 
If you still have questions after reviewing these pages, please send e-mail to <a href="mailto:GrantQuestion@msdeved.isu.edu">GrantQuestion@msdeved.isu.edu</a>.  The Instructional Grant Program is currently limited to higher education institutions in the United States & Canada.  High schools will be considered on a case by case basis.
<P>  
</font>
<font size=3><a name="01">
<b>Grant Description and Requirements</b></a></font>
<font size=2>
<P> 
The Instructional Grant Program includes three levels of grant awards.  Microsoft will provide licenses for applications, developer language products, and operating systems.  The number and type of licenses awarded is dependent upon the level of the grant.  For 1997, the levels are:
<P> 
<table border=1 cellpadding=5>
<td align=left valign=top><font size="2">Level 1</font></td>
<td align=left valign=top><font size="2">Course Development Grant</font></td></tr>
<tr><td align=left valign=top><font size="2">Level 2</font></td>
<td align=left valign=top><font size="2">Team Builder/Infrastructure Development Grant</font></td></tr>	
<tr><td align=left valign=top><font size="2">Level 3</font></td>
<td align=left valign=top><font size="2">Professional Development Grant</font></td></tr></table>
<P>		

Each department within a school is eligible to apply for the grant level of their choice.  The grant application and supporting materials must meet the requirements detailed below to be eligible for the level requested.  If an application does not meet the higher-level criteria, Microsoft may fund you at one of the lower levels if your application meets the requirements of that level.
<P>

Software available varies by level of award and is listed below. Schools will be required to purchase an initial copy of each of their selected software applications from their local reseller. Microsoft provides the additional licenses under this grant program. 
<P>

All levels of grants require course materials to be classified by Knowledge Groups. Knowledge Groups are  categories for classifying curricula traditionally covered in the technical areas -- Computer Science, Information Systems, and Software Engineering.  Each course taught may be categorized by one of the Knowledge Groups.  Courses can then be further categorized by the Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs) subsections for each Knowledge Group.  KSAs match the objectives of a course and are the fundamental building blocks of any curriculum.  We have defined Knowledge Groups and KSAs using the ACM draft standards for Computer Science and Information Systems curricula.  For more information about Knowledge Groups, see the Grant Application and related Help file.
<P>


<table border=1 cellpadding=5>
<tr>
