<P>

<font size=3>
<b>The Campus Z-Station Program and the Programmer's Dream Pack</b>
</font>

<P>

<font size=2>
The  <a href="http://www.zds.com">Campus Z-Station&reg; Program</a> -- developed by Zenith Data Systems (ZDS) with 
Microsoft -- gives you and your students direct access to low-priced hardware.

What's more, when you order the Z-Station, you can save substantially on the Programmer's Dream Pack.
<p>

<IMG SRC="gifs/zheader.gif" ALT="Campus Z-Station Program" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="425" HEIGHT="106" BORDER="0">

<p> 

Choose from a variety of Z-Station Pentium&reg; systems, each preconfigured 
with the Microsoft&reg; Windows&reg; 95 operating system and Microsoft Office 
software, as well as other first-class software products and tools. The 
Campus Z-Station Program is a great way for you to build -- or add to -- a 
computer lab at your school.
</font>

