<P>

<font size=2>
<b>Evaluate products for your classes</b>
<br>
To give faculty the opportunity to preview and evaluate Microsoft&reg; development 
tools for your curriculum, we've set up a <a href="eval.html">Faculty Product Evaluation Program</a> at the 
Academic Cooperative Web Site. Choose Visual C++&reg;, Visual Basic&reg;, Visual J++&#153;, 
Windows&reg; 95, or Windows NT&reg;, include a brief description of the course where 
you will be using the software, and we'll send you the product to evaluate. 

<P>

<b>Save big money with academic pricing</b>
<br>


All of our Windows and Internet development tools are specially priced for 
our academic customers, including volume licenses. To 
order, contact your local Microsoft Authorized Education Reseller (AER). 
For information about an AER in your area, please call (800) 621-7930.

<p>

</font><font size=3><b>Languages and Tools</b></font><font size=2>

<P>

<a name="prices">
<b>Microsoft Visual C++ 4.0</b></a>

<BR>
Visual C++ supports 16-bit and 32-bit 
programming and is fully compatible with Windows 95 and Windows NT. Version 4.0 
is fully ANSI C compliant and includes the latest C++ features, including 
templates, exception handling, run-time type information, namespaces, the 
Standard Template Library, an optimizing compiler, and Microsoft Developer 
Studio. Plus, the Microsoft Foundation Class Library is loaded with new 
features. (The package also includes Visual C++ version 1.52 for 16-bit 
development and Mastering Visual C++.)
</font>
<P>

