<tr><td colspan="6">

<P><br>
<h3>Academic Cooperative<br>Faculty Speakers Program</h3>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Join the Academic Cooperative Faculty Speaker's Program
and get a $200 stipend when you share your expertise about integrating
Microsoft Visual Tools technology in the curriculum at conferences,
seminars, and regional events.  We're looking for computer science,
engineering, business, information systems, and math faculty who
want to share their technology innovations  and knowledge with
their academic colleagues. If you're planning to attend a discipline-focused
conference or event and wish to demonstrate or present your programs
and our tools, you're eligible.  Just follow the instructions
below.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>To qualify for the Academic Cooperative Faculty
Speaker's Program:</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>You must complete the <a href="#application">application</a> below for each
individual event that you plan to present.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Send proof of your participation and/or presentation
acceptance by the official conference entity at least 30 days
before the event. (If there isn't a &quot;formal&quot; acceptance
letter, you can send us all of the information on your school
letterhead.)  Proof or letters go to:</FONT>
</UL>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The Academic Cooperative</FONT>
<br>
<FONT SIZE=2>Microsoft</FONT>
<br>
<FONT SIZE=2>One Microsoft Way, Building 5/1093</FONT>
<br>
<FONT SIZE=2>Redmond, WA  98052-6399</FONT>
<UL>
<p>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Include the innovative use of Microsoft tools
in your presentation or demonstration.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Conferences supported should be relevant to higher
education faculty members from the disciplines listed above.</FONT>
</UL>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2></FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>What happens next?:</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Fill out the on-line application at least 30
days before the speaking engagement.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>All incoming applications will be evaluated on
an ongoing basis throughout the year.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Email to <a href="mailto:FacultySpeakers@msdeved.isu.edu">FacultySpeakers@msdeved.isu.edu</a> a short synopsis (250-500 words) of your planned presentation.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>If your application is accepted, you will be
notified by e-mail.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Once you have completed the speaking engagement,
you must return to the Academic Cooperative Site and fill out the
<a href="/ms/fspcomplete.html"> completion notice</a>.  At that time, the check generating  procedure
will begin and a check will be sent to you at the address on the
application. </FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>Remember, you will not receive the stipend prior
to the event, but will receive it 2-4 weeks after you have filled
out the completion notice.</FONT><br>
</UL>
</td></tr>

