<TITLE>Online Access</TITLE>
<H2>Online Access</H2>
<hr>
OTA has taken advantage of recent developments in information 
technologies to make its work widely available electronically.  General 
information about the agency, electronic versions of  OTA publications, 
and news about work in progress all are accessible online.  You can 
retrieve this information in a variety of ways.<P>

<UL>
<LI><B>Internet Access</B>: You can use any of these Internet tools:
<UL>
<LI>World Wide Web: <A HREF="http://gandalf.isu.edu/ota/ota.html">http:
//bilbo.isu.edu/ota/ota.html</A>
<LI>FTP: <A HREF="ftp://bilbo.isu.edu/">ftp://gandalf.isu.edu/</A>,
 login as anonymous,
password is your e-mail address.  Publications are in the /ota directory.
<LI>Windows GUI: <A HREF="ftp://gandalf.isu.edu/">
ftp://bilbo.isu.edu/</A>, login as anonymous and mget files
 and installation instructions.  Files are in the /pub/ota/team directory.
</UL>
</UL>
