<TITLE>Congressional Resources</TITLE>

<H1>Congressional Resources</H1>
<HR>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF = "gopher://marvel.loc.gov:70/1">Library of Congress MARVEL</A>:  Machine assisted realization of the virtual electronic library. <I>MARVEL</I> is a Campus-Wide Information System that combines the vast collection of information available about the Library with easy access to diverse electronic resources over the internet.
<LI><A HREF = "http://thomas.loc.gov">THOMAS</A>:  <I>THOMAS</I> is an online public access system of congressional information. <I>THOMAS</I> marks the first time that people both here and abroad can gain access to a wide range of information about American laws and lawmakers through the Library of Congress's World Wide Web Server.
<LI><A HREF = "http://www.house.gov">The U.S. House of Representatives' World Wide Web</A>:  Provides public access to legislative information as well as information about Members, Committees, and Organizations of the House and to other U.S. government information
resources. 
<LI><A HREF = "gopher://gopher.house.gov:70/1">House</A> and <A HREF = "gopher://ftp.senate.gov:70/11/">Senate</A>:  Rapidly growing Gopher servers for both houses of Congress. Testimony and basic contact information.

</UL>

