<head>
<title>Kregg Aytes</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h1><img src="images/isu_logo.gif" align=bottom width=46 height=109></h1>
<h1>Home Page for Kregg Aytes</h1>
<h4>Kregg Aytes</h4>
<h4>Assistant Professor</h4>
<h4><a href="http://cob.isu.edu/page20.html">Computer Information Systems Department</a></h4>
<h4><a href="http://cob.isu.edu/">College of Business</a> </h4>
<h4><a href="http://www.isu.edu/">Idaho State University</a></h4>
<h4>Pocatello, ID 83209</h4>
<p>Email: <a href="mailto: aytekreg@isu.edu">aytekreg@isu.edu</a> </p>
<p><img src="images/rainban.gif" align=bottom width=600 height=5> </p>
<h2>Teaching</h2>
<p>I have been at ISU since Fall, 1993. In that time, I have taught numerous courses, including </p>
<ul>
<li>CIS 220 - Foundations of Computer Programming </li>
<li><a href="http://cob.isu.edu/classes/cis/cis382/">CIS 382 - Systems Analysis and Design </a></li>
<li>CIS 480 - Database Management Systems </li>
<li><a href="http://cob.isu.edu/classes/cis/cis490/">CIS 490 - Management of Information Systems</a> </li>
<li>MBA 614 - Graduate-level MIS course </li>
<li><a href="http://cwis.isu.edu/~aytekreg/660/660syl.htm">MBA 660 - Technology to Support Teams</a> </li>
</ul>
<p>My <a href="http://cwis.isu.edu/~aytekreg/cob.htm">Business student Websites</a> page includes pointers to several categories of websites, including those that may be of interest to CIS, accounting, finance, 
marketing, and management students. Take a look - there are some good resources in there! </p>
<p><img src="images/rainban.gif" align=bottom width=600 height=5> </p>
<h2>Research</h2>
<p>Much of my research revolves around investigations into the effective use of collaborative technologies. Fortunately, there is a wealth of information out there on the 
web about such things. To see some of what is available, go to the <a href="group.htm">Groupware page</a>. </p>
<p><img src="images/rainban.gif" align=bottom width=600 height=5> </p>
<h2>Personal Interests</h2>
<p>When I'm not working, I like to spend my time with my wife, Tracy, and our two kids, Erica (age 11), and Logan (age 9). I enjoy running, x-country skiing, 
mountain biking, and an occasional tennis match. I'm also learning to downhill and telemark ski, although currently I'm pretty lousy. </p>
</body>

</html>
