<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6>CIS 220<BR>
</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Arial">Course Objectives<BR>
</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>At the completion of this course, you should have
a strong foundation in the principles of structured programming
and increased exposure to critical thinking and technology.  Specifically,
this course introduces the techniques for good programming practice,
and provides the basis for learning more about the processing
of data and file structures in CIS 221.<BR>
</FONT>
<H1><FONT SIZE=2>The above objectives can only be obtained through
experience with a programming language.  Therefore, you will spend
<I>considerable </I>effort in this course designing, coding, and
debugging Visual Basic 4.0 programs.  While the concepts taught
in this course are relatively simple, when used together in a
large program the cognitive complexity of their interrelations
can be challenging and time consuming.</FONT></H1>

<H1><FONT SIZE=4>Class Times<BR>
</FONT></H1>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>  Section 01: BA408 - 11:00 MW  Final: Mon. 16Dec.
10:30</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2> Section 02:  BA208 - 08:00 TTH Final: Tues. 17Dec.
  7:30</FONT>
<H1>Office Hours<BR>
