</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=295>Drive List Box</TD><TD WIDTH=295>DRV</TD></TR>

</TABLE>

<H1>Appendix III: Sample Code</H1>

<H2>Sample #1: Sorting an Array</H2>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Procedure Name:  SortArray</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Programmer:      Nathan Wingert - modified by
David Beard 21Aug96</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Version:         Paradigm Version 1.1</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Description:     Sorts the array passed to the
procedure by the variable Stamp defined in</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'*   the global record type REC_SortArray</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Globals used: REC_SortArray</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Sub SortArray (P_SortArr() As REC_SortArray)<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim Temp As REC_SortArray</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim Sorted, sortLength, i as integer<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>On Error GoTo sort_commands_error<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>sorted = False<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>sortLength = Ubound(P_SortArr, 1) - 1<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>While sorted = False</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>    sorted = True</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>    For i = 1 To sortLength            'Assume that
the array starting bound is = 1<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>        If P_SortArr(i).Stamp &gt; P_SortArr(i+1).Stamp
Then</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>            Temp = P_SortArr(i)</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>            P_SortArr(i) = P_SortArr(i + 1)</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>            P_SortArr(i + 1) = Temp</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>            sorted = False</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>        End If<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>    Next i</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>    sort_length = sort_length - 1</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Wend</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>End Sub</FONT>
<H2>Sample #2:  Reading a random access file</H2>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Procedure Name:  ReadRandom</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Programmer:      Nathan Wingert - modified by
David Beard 21Aug96</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Description:      Reads a random access file and
places the data in as list box</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Globals:     This function uses the global type
declaration:  REC_Bin</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'*</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'*                        Type  REC_Bin</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'*   SSN as string * 20</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'*   Name as string * 40</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'*  End Type</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Sub ReadRandom (P_LSTFileDisp as control, P_FileName
as string<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim fileRec as REC_Bin</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim Fhdl as integer</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim FileLength, I as integer<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>FHdl = FreeFile           'get a valid file handle
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Open P_FileName for random access as FHdl Len=Len(fileRec)
               'Open the file<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>FileLength = Lof(FHdl) / Len(FileRec)   'get the
length of the file in records<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>For I = 1 to FileLength</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Get #FHdl, I, fileRec                   'get the
file record<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'Add the data to the list box<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>P_LSTFileDisp. AddItem Trim$(fileRec.SSN)  &amp;
Chr$(9) &amp; Trim$(fileRec.Name)</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Next I<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Close FHdl<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>End Sub</FONT>
<H2>Sample #3:  Reading a Sequential File (Method 1)</H2>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Procedure Name:  ReadText</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Programmer:      Nathan Wingert as modified by
David Beard 21Aug96</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Description:     Reads a sequential file one-line
at a time into a multi-line text box</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Sub ReadText (P_TXTFileDisp as Control, P_FileName
as String)<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim Fhdl as integer</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim TempTest as String<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>FHdl=FreeFile</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Open P_FileName for input as FHdl<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>While Not EOF(FHdl)</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Line Input #FHdl, TempText</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>P_TXTFileDisp.SelStart = Len(P_TXTFileDisp.Text)
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>P_TXTFileDisp.SelText = TempText</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Wend<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Close FHdl<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>End Sub</FONT>
<H2>Sample #4:  Reading a Sequential File (Method 2)</H2>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Procedure Name:  ReadText</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Programmer:      Nathan Wingert - modified by
David Beard 221Aug96</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'* Description:     Reads a sequential file into
a multi-line text box all at once</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>'************************************************************************</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Sub ReadText (P_TXTFileDisp as Control, P_FileName
as String)</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Dim Fhdl as integer<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>FHdl=FreeFile<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Open P_FileName for input as FHdl<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>P_TXTFileDisp.Text = Input$(LOF(FHdl), FHdl)<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Close FHdl<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>End Sub</FONT>
<H1>Appendix IV: Visual Basic Command Reference</H1>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The following is a summary of commands used in the
Visual Basic programming language.  This does not represent an
entire set of visual basic commands.  It is intended as an search
mechanism to facilitate the use of the windows help system when
locating commands.  Browse the list to locate a definition that
resembles what you want to accomplish then search the help files
for the command listed for detailed information.  Happy Hunting.
<BR>
</FONT>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91><B>Command</B></TD><TD WIDTH=216><B>Syntax</B>
</TD><TD WIDTH=283><B>Description</B></TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>ASC</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Asc(stringexpression)</TD>
<TD WIDTH=283>Return the ASCII value of the first character of the stored string
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Chr$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Chr[$](charcode)</TD>
<TD WIDTH=283>Generate a character based in an ASCII value.</TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Close</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Close [[#]filenumber] [,[#]filenumber] . . .
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Close a file</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Date$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Date[$]</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns the current Date/Time 
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Dim</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Dim varname[([subscripts])][As [New] type][, varname[([subscripts])][As [New] type] ] . . .
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Declare a variable for use</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Do / Until</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Do
<P>
 [statementblock]
<P>
 [Exit Do]
<P>
 [statementblock]
<P>
Loop [Until condition
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>like while except condition is compared AFTER first execution.  See While.
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>DoEvents</TD><TD WIDTH=216>DoEvents( )</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Execute all other pending process (other programs) before continuing operation (used to allow background processing).
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>For / Next</TD><TD WIDTH=216>For counter = start To end [ Step increment ]
<P>
 [statementblock]
<P>
 [Exit For]
<P>
 [statementblock]
<P>
Next [counter [, counter][, ...]]
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>For Next Statement</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Format$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Format[$](expression[, fmt] )
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Format a string / number to a given mask (Add $ to Dollar amounts, add - to a phone number).
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>FreeFile</TD><TD WIDTH=216>FreeFile [( )]</TD>
<TD WIDTH=283>Returns an unused file handle for the &quot;Open&quot; and &quot;Close&quot; commands
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Get</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Get [#] filenumber,[recordnumber],variablename
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Get a record from a random access file</TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Global </TD><TD WIDTH=216>Global varname[([subscripts])] [As [New] type] [, varname[([subscripts])] [As [New] type] ] . . .
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Declare a global variable for use</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Global Const</TD><TD WIDTH=216>[Global] Const constantname = expression [, constantname = expression] . . .
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Declare a global constant</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>If ... Then</TD><TD WIDTH=216>If condition1  Then
<P>
 [statementblock-1]
<P>
[ElseIf condition2 Then
<P>
 [statementblock-2] ]
<P>
[Else
<P>
 [statementblock-n] ]
<P>
End If
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Standard If - Then clause</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Input</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Input[$](n,[#]filenumber)
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Reads a section from a sequential file (to the next delimiter).
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Input Box</TD><TD WIDTH=216></TD><TD WIDTH=283>Displays an input dialog with a text entry field and a description area.
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>InStr</TD><TD WIDTH=216>InStr( [start,] strexpr1, strexpr2 )
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Searches a string for a substring and returns the starting position
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Kill</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Kill filespec</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Delete a file
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Lbound</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Lbound(array [,dimension])
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns the smallest available subscript for the indicated dimension of an array.
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Lcase$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>LCase[$](stringexpr)
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Converts a given string to all lower case</TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Left$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Left[$](strexpr, n)</TD>
<TD WIDTH=283>Returns the left &quot;Length&quot; characters of a given string
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Len</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Len(strexpr)</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns the length of a string
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Line Input</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Line Input # filenumber, variablename
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Reads an entire line from a sequential file
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Lof</TD><TD WIDTH=216>LOF(filenumber)</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns the length of an open  file in bytes
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Ltrim$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>[L | R]Trim[$](stringexpr)
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Trim only the spaces to the left of the string
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Mid$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Mid[$](stringexpr, start[, length])
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns a substring of a given string.</TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Now</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Now</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns the current Date/Time Numeric Code (Double)
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Open</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Open file [For mode] [Access access] [lock] As [#]filenumber [Len = reclen]
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Open a text or random access file</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Put</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Put [#] filenumber, [recordnumber], variablename
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Store a record to a random access file</TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>ReDim</TD><TD WIDTH=216>ReDim [Preserve] varname(subscripts) [As type][, varname(subscripts) [As type] ] . . .
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Resize or redimension a memory array (see Dim)
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Right$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Right[$](stringexpr, n)
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns the right most characters of a given string
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Rtrim$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>[L | R]Trim[$](stringexpr)
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Trim only the spaces to the right with in the given string.
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Select Case</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Select Case testexpression
<P>
[Case expressionlist1
<P>
 [statementblock-1] ]
<P>
[Case expressionlist2
<P>
 [statementblock-2] ]
<P>
[Case Else
<P>
 [statementblock-n] ]
<P>
End Select
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Execute various options based on the value of a given variable
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Str$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Str[$](number)</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Converts a string to a number
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Trim$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>[L | R]Trim[$](stringexpr)
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Trim leading a trailing spaces of a string
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Ubound</TD><TD WIDTH=216>UBound(array [, dimension])
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Returns the largest available subscript for the indicated dimension of an array.
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Ucase$</TD><TD WIDTH=216>UCase[$](stringexpr)
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>Converts a given string to all upper case</TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>Val</TD><TD WIDTH=216>Val(stringexpression)</TD>
<TD WIDTH=283>Convert a string to a numeric value</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=91>While / Wend</TD><TD WIDTH=216>While condition
<P>
 [statementblock]
<P>
Wend
</TD><TD WIDTH=283>While Statement.  Condition is checked BEFORE any code in the loop is executed (see Do / Until)
</TD></TR>

</TABLE>

