<B><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=4><P>Appendix II: Variable Naming Standards</P>
</FONT><I><FONT FACE="Arial"><P>Variable Naming Standards</P><DIR>
<DIR>

</B></I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2><P>Variables of the specified type should begin with the specific extension followed by a variable name that matches the function of the variable.  Please note this is not an inclusive list of all variable types in Visual Basic.  Other types are the discretion of the individual programmer.  These are defined to ease the debugging and grading processes.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></DIR>
</DIR>
</FONT>
<TABLE BORDER CELLSPACING=2 CELLPADDING=7 WIDTH=590>
