<TITLE>OTA's Environment Program</TITLE>
<H2>Environment</H2>
<hr>
The Environment Program assesses scientific, technical, and 
policy issues related to the environment.  Program areas include 
the use and conservation of renewable resources; pollution prevention, 
control and remediation; and environmental health and risk management. 
 Assessments have focused on such topics as agriculture; management 
of public lands; biological diversity; risk assessment methods and 
policy; air and water pollution; management of solid, hazardous, 
and nuclear wastes; and the effects of weather and climate change.
<P>
<P>
