<TITLE>Document Types</TITLE>
<H2>Document Types</H2>
<hr>
<b><I>Reports</I></b> are the principal documentation of formal assessment projects.  
OTA Reports are analyses with major policy content.  They are submitted 
to the Technology Assessment Board for review prior to release.  Major 
policy content includes not only policy options, but also conclusions 
that are virtually indistinguishable from policy options, and significant 
analysis directly relevant to policy alternatives.  The Technology 
Assessment Board has the opportunity to review Reports before release 
but this does not necessarily imply endorsement of the results by the 
Board or its individual members.<p>

<b><I>Background Papers</I></b> are analyses without major policy content.  A Background 
Paper presents information that generally stems from, or supplements, OTA 
assessments, covers a specific topic not immediately related to an assessment, 
or is an outcome of internal exploratory planning and evaluation.

<HR>
