<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">GOVERNMENTAL AND NOT-FOR-PROFIT
ACCOUNTING</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Accounting 460, Spring 1997</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">EXPANDED COURSE SYLLABUS<BR>
</FONT></CENTER>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Introduction</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce students
to the operating characteristics and environment of not-for-profit
entities that distinguish them from for-profit entities. </FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 1 </FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Principles of Accounting and Financial
Reporting for State and Local Governments</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce the basic
principles of accounting and financial reporting, with a special
emphasis on the measurement focus and basis of accounting, for
state and local governments.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 2</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E2-2, E2-5</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Budgeting for General and Special Revenue
Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce students
to the budgetary accounting and reporting concepts.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 3</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Q3-2, Q3-3, E3-4, E3-2, E3-7</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Accounting for General and Special Revenue
Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions applicable to the
general and special revenue funds that are encountered by typical
governmental entities. </FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 4</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E4-8, E4-9, E4-10, E4-2</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Capital Project Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions applicable to capital
project funds that are encountered by typical governmental entities.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 5</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E5-2, E5-5</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Debt Service Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions applicable to debt
service funds that are encountered by typical governmental entities.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 7</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E7-2, E7-7 [omit (b)], E7-18</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">General Fixed Assets </FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce the use
of the General Fixed Asset Account Group and to illustrate its
interaction with the governmental funds.</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 6</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E6-2, E6-4, E7-7(b)</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">General Long-Term Debt Account Groups</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce the use
of the Genral Long-Term Debt Account Group and to illustrate its
interaction with the governmental funds.</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 8</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E8-2, E8-6, E8-7</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Internal Service Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions typically accounted
for in internal service funds.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 9</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Q9-3, E9-2, E9-7, E9-8(a)</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Enterprise Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions typically accounted
for in enterprise funds.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 10</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Q10-1, Q10-4, E10-2, E10-5, E10-6</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Cash Flow Statements</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to learn the preparation
of a cash flow statement for governmental entities.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E9-8(b), E10-7(a)</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Agency Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions typically accounted
for in an agency fund.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 11</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Q11-2, E11-2, E11-6, E11-7</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Trust Funds</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions typically accounted
for in expendable and nonexpendable trust funds.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 12</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Q12-1, E12-2, E12-5</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Public Employee Retirement Systems</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions typically encountered
in a public employee retirement system and to understand the reporting
limitations of the current reporting for such systems.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 12</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E12-8</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">FASB #116</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce revenue
recognition requirements for contributions made and received by
non-governmental organizations.</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">FASB #117</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce financial
reporting requirements for non-governmental not-for-profit organizations.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Colleges and Universities</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions typically encountered
by governmentally-owned colleges and universities.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 19</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E19-1, E19-4, E19-7</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Health Care Entities</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to apply generally accepted
accounting principles to specific transactions typically entered
into by governmentally-owned health care entities.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Chapter 20</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>E20-1, E20-2</FONT>
<HR>

<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Federal Government Agencies</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce the concepts
and standards of accounting as promulgated by the Comptroller
General of the United States for use by agencies of the U. S.
Government.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 15</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E15-1, E15-2, E15-7</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Audits of State and Local Governmental
Entities</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The purpose is to introduce the specialized
audit reports issued by independent accountants conducting audits
of state and local governmental entities.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Chapter 14</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">E14-1, E14-4</FONT>
<HR>

</BODY>

</HTML>
